cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as named entity recognition and morphological disambiguation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a joint learning model for NER and MD taggers. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of an AI system (NER tagger) by incorporating linguistic features. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper employs neural network models for joint learning. 
- cs.DL (Deep Learning) is also a possible category as the paper employs deep learning models for joint learning.
